verses.text_plain: The burden of Damascus. Behold, Damascus is taken away from being a city, and it shall be a ruinous heap.
verses.verse_html: 1The burden of Damascus. Behold, Damascus is taken away from being a city, and it shall be a ruinous heap.

tokens.text: and it shall be a ruinous

verses.text_plain: The cities of Aroer are forsaken: they shall be for flocks, which shall lie down, and none shall make them afraid.
verses.verse_html: 2The cities of Aroer are forsaken: they shall be for flocks, which shall lie down, and none shall make them afraid.

verses.text_plain: The fortress also shall cease from Ephraim, and the kingdom from Damascus, and the remnant of Syria: they shall be as the glory of the children of Israel, saith the Lord of hosts.
verses.verse_html: 3The fortress also shall cease from Ephraim, and the kingdom from Damascus, and the remnant of Syria: they shall be as the glory of the children of Israel, saith the Lord of hosts.

tokens.text: they shall be as the glory

verses.text_plain: And in that day it shall come to pass, that the glory of Jacob shall be made thin, and the fatness of his flesh shall wax lean.
verses.verse_html: 4And in that day it shall come to pass, that the glory of Jacob shall be made thin, and the fatness of his flesh shall wax lean.

verses.text_plain: And it shall be as when the harvestman gathereth the corn, and reapeth the ears with his arm; and it shall be as he that gathereth ears in the valley of Rephaim.
verses.verse_html: 5And it shall be as when the harvestman gathereth the corn, and reapeth the ears with his arm; and it shall be as he that gathereth ears in the valley of Rephaim.

tokens.text: And it shall be as when the harvestman
and it shall be as he that gathereth

verses.text_plain: Yet gleaning grapes shall be left in it, as the shaking of an olive tree, two or three berries in the top of the uppermost bough, four or five in the outmost fruitful branches thereof, saith the Lord God of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 6Yet gleaning grapes shall be left in it, as the shaking of an olive tree, two or three berries in the top of the uppermost bough, four or five in the outmost fruitful branches thereof, saith the Lord God of Israel.

verses.text_plain: At that day shall a man look to his Maker, and his eyes shall have respect to the Holy One of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 7At that day shall a man look to his Maker, and his eyes shall have respect to the Holy One of Israel.

verses.text_plain: And he shall not look to the altars, the work of his hands, neither shall respect that which his fingers have made, either the groves, or the images.
verses.verse_html:
8And he shall not look to the altars, the work of his hands, neither shall respect that which his fingers have made, either the groves, or the images.
 images: or, sun images

footnotes.body_html: images: or, sun images

verses.text_plain: In that day shall his strong cities be as a forsaken bough, and an uppermost branch, which they left because of the children of Israel: and there shall be desolation.
verses.verse_html: 9In that day shall his strong cities be as a forsaken bough, and an uppermost branch, which they left because of the children of Israel: and there shall be desolation.

verses.text_plain: Because thou hast forgotten the God of thy salvation, and hast not been mindful of the rock of thy strength, therefore shalt thou plant pleasant plants, and shalt set it with strange slips:
verses.verse_html: 10Because thou hast forgotten the God of thy salvation, and hast not been mindful of the rock of thy strength, therefore shalt thou plant pleasant plants, and shalt set it with strange slips:

verses.text_plain: In the day shalt thou make thy plant to grow, and in the morning shalt thou make thy seed to flourish: but the harvest shall be a heap in the day of grief and of desperate sorrow.
verses.verse_html:
11In the day shalt thou make thy plant to grow, and in the morning shalt thou make thy seed to flourish: but the harvest shall be a heap in the day of grief and of desperate sorrow.
 a heap: or, removed in the day of inheritance, and there shall be deadly sorrow

footnotes.body_text: a heap: or, removed in the day of inheritance, and there shall be deadly sorrow
footnotes.body_html: a heap: or, removed in the day of inheritance, and there shall be deadly sorrow

verses.text_plain: Woe to the multitude of many people, which make a noise like the noise of the seas; and to the rushing of nations, that make a rushing like the rushing of mighty waters!
verses.verse_html:
12Woe to the multitude of many people, which make a noise like the noise of the seas; and to the rushing of nations, that make a rushing like the rushing of mighty waters!
 multitude: or, noise
 ,
 mighty: or, many

tokens.text: make a rushing like the rushing

verses.text_plain: The nations shall rush like the rushing of many waters: but God shall rebuke them, and they shall flee far off, and shall be chased as the chaff of the mountains before the wind, and like a rolling thing before the whirlwind.
verses.verse_html:
13The nations shall rush like the rushing of many waters: but God shall rebuke them, and they shall flee far off, and shall be chased as the chaff of the mountains before the wind, and like a rolling thing before the whirlwind.
 a rolling: or, thistledown

footnotes.body_html: a rolling: or, thistledown

verses.text_plain: And behold at eveningtide trouble; and before the morning he is not. This is the portion of them that spoil us, and the lot of them that rob us.
verses.verse_html: 14And behold at eveningtide trouble; and before the morning he is not. This is the portion of them that spoil us, and the lot of them that rob us.
